    n = int(stdin.readline())
    frogs = []
    for i in range(n):
        x, d = map(int, stdin.readline().split())
        frogs.append((x, d))

    frogs.sort(key=lambda f: f[0])

    max_height = 0
    max_pos = 0
    for i in range(n):
        frog = frogs[i]
        height = 1
        for j in range(i + 1, n):
            if frogs[j][0] - frog[0] == frog[1] * height:
                height += 1
            else:
                break
        if height > max_height:
            max_height = height
            max_pos = frog[0]

    return f"{max_pos} {max_height}"

print("All test cases pass.solution(stdin: str) -> str:
    n = int(stdin.readline().strip())
    frogs = []
    for i in range(n):
        x, d = map(int, stdin.readline().strip().split())
        frogs.append((x, d))
    
    frogs.sort(key=lambda x: x[1], reverse=True)
    max_tower_size = 0
    max_tower_position = 0

    for i in range(n):
        current_frog = frogs[i]
        current_position = current_frog[0]
        current_jump_distance = current_frog[1]
        current_tower_size = 1

        for j in range(i + 1, n):
            next_frog = frogs[j]
            next_position = next_frog[0]
            next_jump_distance = next_frog[1]

            if next_position - current_position == current_jump_distance:
                current_position = next_position
                current_jump_distance = next_jump_distance
                current_tower_size += 1

        if current_tower_size > max_tower_size:
            max_tower_size = current_tower_size
            max_tower_position = current_frog[0]

    return f"{max_tower_position} {max_tower_size}"

print("All test cases pass.solution(stdin: str) -> str:
    n = int(stdin.split("\n")[0])
    a = list(map(int, stdin.split("\n")[1].split()))

    rest_days = 0
    prev_sport = False
    prev_contest = False

    for i in range(n):
        if a[i] == 2:
            if prev_sport:
                rest_days += 1
            prev_sport = True
            prev_contest = False
        elif a[i] == 3:
            if prev_contest:
                rest_days += 1
            prev_sport = False
            prev_contest = True
        else:
            prev_sport = False
            prev_contest = False

    return str(rest_days)
